As mentioned in [ACTION_BUTTON_PRESS](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/MotionEvent#ACTION_BUTTON_PRESS)&#39;s documentation:
&gt; This action is not a touch event so it is delivered to View#onGenericMotionEvent(MotionEvent) rather than View#onTouchEvent(MotionEvent).

Same is valid for the [ACTION_BUTTON_RELEASE](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/MotionEvent#ACTION_BUTTON_RELEASE) event. These events are probably used for physical button events.  

You must use the [ACTION_DOWN](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/MotionEvent#ACTION_DOWN) for press event and [ACTION_UP](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/MotionEvent#ACTION_UP) for release event instead, for touch events.  

So modify your code as following:
```lang-java
if (event.getAction() == MotionEvent.ACTION_DOWN) {
    itemView.startAnimation(Animations.back);
} else if (event.getAction() == MotionEvent.ACTION_UP) {
    // ...
} else return false;
```

